# Plan: Custom Theme System for T3 Code

## Context

T3 Code currently supports light/dark/system mode toggling (managed by `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`) but has no named color-theme system. Users can't choose from distinct, branded palettes. This plan adds a full named theme system: shared type definitions in `packages/shared`, a React hook following the existing `useSyncExternalStore` pattern, a `ThemeSelector` component, and wires it into the settings page.

The existing `useTheme` (dark/light/system toggle) is left **unchanged** — the new color theme system sits alongside it.

---

## Architecture

```
packages/shared/src/themes.ts          ← Theme types + 3 built-in themes + getTheme/listThemes
  ↑ imported by
apps/web/src/hooks/useColorTheme.ts    ← useSyncExternalStore hook, applies CSS vars + .dark class
  ↑ used by
apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx   ← Radio-style picker with color swatches
  ↑ rendered in
apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx      ← Existing settings page (Appearance section)
  + early init import in
apps/web/src/main.tsx                       ← Ensures theme applies before React renders
```

---

## Critical Files

| File | Action |
|------|--------|
| `packages/shared/src/themes.ts` | **Create** |
| `packages/shared/package.json` | **Modify** — add `./themes` export |
| `apps/web/src/hooks/useColorTheme.ts` | **Create** |
| `apps/web/src/index.css` | **Modify** — add new CSS vars for sidebar/editor/terminal/statusBar |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` | **Create** |
| `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` | **Modify** — import and render ThemeSelector |
| `apps/web/src/main.tsx` | **Modify** — add side-effect import to init theme before React renders |

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — `packages/shared/src/themes.ts`

Plain TypeScript (no Effect), matching the single-responsibility module pattern of `model.ts`, `git.ts`, etc.

```ts
export interface ThemeColors {
  background: string;
  foreground: string;
  accent: string;
  sidebar: string;
  editor: string;
  terminal: string;
  statusBar: string;
}

export interface Theme {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  colors: ThemeColors;
  fontFamily: string;
  fontSize: number;
  isDark: boolean;   // needed to toggle .dark class on <html>
}

export const BUILT_IN_THEMES: readonly Theme[] = [
  {
    id: "t3-dark",
    name: "T3 Dark",
    isDark: true,
    fontFamily: '"DM Sans", system-ui, sans-serif',
    fontSize: 14,
    colors: {
      background: "oklch(0.145 0 0)",       // matches CSS: color-mix(neutral-950 95%, white)
      foreground: "oklch(0.95 0 0)",         // neutral-100
      accent:     "oklch(0.588 0.217 264)",  // existing dark --primary blue
      sidebar:    "oklch(0.12 0 0)",
      editor:     "oklch(0.145 0 0)",
      terminal:   "oklch(0.10 0 0)",
      statusBar:  "oklch(0.18 0 0)",
    },
  },
  {
    id: "t3-light",
    name: "T3 Light",
    isDark: false,
    fontFamily: '"DM Sans", system-ui, sans-serif',
    fontSize: 14,
    colors: {
      background: "oklch(1 0 0)",            // white
      foreground: "oklch(0.32 0 0)",         // neutral-800
      accent:     "oklch(0.488 0.217 264)",  // existing light --primary blue
      sidebar:    "oklch(0.97 0 0)",
      editor:     "oklch(1 0 0)",
      terminal:   "oklch(0.95 0 0)",
      statusBar:  "oklch(0.94 0 0)",
    },
  },
  {
    id: "t3-midnight",
    name: "T3 Midnight",
    isDark: true,
    fontFamily: '"DM Sans", system-ui, sans-serif',
    fontSize: 14,
    colors: {
      background: "oklch(0.13 0.04 280)",   // deep blue-purple
      foreground: "oklch(0.92 0.02 270)",   // light blue-tinted white
      accent:     "oklch(0.65 0.20 295)",   // vivid purple-indigo
      sidebar:    "oklch(0.10 0.05 285)",
      editor:     "oklch(0.14 0.04 280)",
      terminal:   "oklch(0.08 0.03 280)",
      statusBar:  "oklch(0.18 0.06 285)",
    },
  },
] as const;

export function listThemes(): readonly Theme[] {
  return BUILT_IN_THEMES;
}

export function getTheme(id: string): Theme | undefined {
  return BUILT_IN_THEMES.find((t) => t.id === id);
}
```

### Step 2 — `packages/shared/package.json`

Add entry to `"exports"`:
```json
"./themes": {
  "types": "./src/themes.ts",
  "import": "./src/themes.ts"
}
```

### Step 3 — `apps/web/src/hooks/useColorTheme.ts`

Mirrors the `useSyncExternalStore` external-store pattern of the existing `useTheme.ts`:

- **Storage key**: `"t3code:color-theme:v1"` (versioned, matching project convention)
- **Default theme**: `"t3-dark"`
- `applyColorTheme(theme)`: 
  - Calls `document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark", theme.isDark)`
  - Calls `document.documentElement.style.setProperty("--background", theme.colors.background)` and same for `--foreground`, `--accent`
  - Calls `document.documentElement.style.setProperty("--sidebar-bg", theme.colors.sidebar)` and same for `--editor-bg`, `--terminal-bg`, `--status-bar-bg`
  - Uses `suppressTransitions` guard (same `.no-transitions` class trick as `useTheme.ts`)
- Module-level IIFE: `applyColorTheme(getStoredTheme())` — applies before React renders
- `subscribe()`: listens for `storage` events (cross-tab sync), cleans up listeners
- `useColorTheme()` returns `{ theme: Theme, setTheme(id: string): void, availableThemes: readonly Theme[] }`
- Import: `import { getTheme, listThemes, BUILT_IN_THEMES } from "@t3tools/shared/themes"`

### Step 4 — `apps/web/src/index.css`

Add the four new CSS custom property declarations to `:root` (with matching dark-mode defaults in `@variant dark`), so components can reference them later:

```css
:root {
  /* … existing vars … */
  --sidebar-bg: var(--color-white);
  --editor-bg:  var(--color-white);
  --terminal-bg: var(--color-neutral-50);
  --status-bar-bg: var(--color-neutral-100);

  @variant dark {
    /* … existing dark vars … */
    --sidebar-bg:    color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 97%, var(--color-white));
    --editor-bg:     color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 95%, var(--color-white));
    --terminal-bg:   var(--color-neutral-950);
    --status-bar-bg: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-900) 90%, var(--color-white));
  }
}
```

### Step 5 — `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx`

Component UI pattern: mirrors the radio-button group in `_chat.settings.tsx` (bordered card rows with "Selected" badge).

Each theme row shows:
- Three color swatches (small `<span>` circles): `colors.background`, `colors.accent`, `colors.sidebar`
- Theme name
- "Selected" badge when active (same `bg-primary/14 text-primary` style as settings page)
- `role="radio"` / `aria-checked` for accessibility

```tsx
import { useColorTheme } from "~/hooks/useColorTheme";

export function ThemeSelector() {
  const { theme, setTheme, availableThemes } = useColorTheme();
  return (
    <div className="space-y-2" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Color theme">
      {availableThemes.map((t) => {
        const selected = theme.id === t.id;
        return (
          <button key={t.id} role="radio" aria-checked={selected}
            className={`flex w-full items-center justify-between rounded-lg border px-3 py-2 text-left transition-colors ${
              selected
                ? "border-primary/60 bg-primary/8 text-foreground"
                : "border-border bg-background text-muted-foreground hover:bg-accent"
            }`}
            onClick={() => setTheme(t.id)}
          >
            <span className="flex items-center gap-2.5">
              {/* Color swatches */}
              <span className="flex gap-1">
                <span className="h-3.5 w-3.5 rounded-full border border-border/40"
                  style={{ background: t.colors.background }} />
                <span className="h-3.5 w-3.5 rounded-full border border-border/40"
                  style={{ background: t.colors.accent }} />
                <span className="h-3.5 w-3.5 rounded-full border border-border/40"
                  style={{ background: t.colors.sidebar }} />
              </span>
              <span className="text-sm font-medium">{t.name}</span>
            </span>
            {selected && (
              <span className="rounded bg-primary/14 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-primary">
                Selected
              </span>
            )}
          </button>
        );
      })}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Step 6 — `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx`

In the **Appearance** section (after line ~208), add a new sub-section **above** the existing dark/light/system radio group:

```tsx
import { ThemeSelector } from "../components/ThemeSelector";

// Inside the <section className="…Appearance…">:
<div className="mb-4">
  <h2 className="text-sm font-medium text-foreground">Color Theme</h2>
  <p className="mt-1 text-xs text-muted-foreground">
    Choose a color palette for the editor.
  </p>
</div>
<ThemeSelector />

// Then a <hr> or <div className="my-4 border-t border-border" />

// Then the existing "Dark Mode" h2 + radio group for system/light/dark
```

### Step 7 — `apps/web/src/main.tsx`

Add one side-effect import at the top (just like importing `./index.css`):

```ts
import "~/hooks/useColorTheme"; // initializes color theme before React renders
```

This ensures `applyColorTheme(getStoredTheme())` runs at module load, before the first React paint, preventing a flash of the wrong theme.

---

## Reused Patterns & References

| Pattern | Source file |
|---------|-------------|
| `useSyncExternalStore` external store | `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` |
| `.no-transitions` flash-suppression | `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` + `apps/web/src/index.css` |
| Versioned localStorage keys (`t3code:...:v1`) | `apps/web/src/appSettings.ts`, `apps/web/src/store.ts` |
| Radio-button selection UI (bordered rows, "Selected" badge) | `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` lines 210–238 |
| Subpath export pattern | `packages/shared/package.json` (all existing entries) |

---

## Verification

1. **Type check**: `bun typecheck` from repo root must pass — the `./themes` export is plain TS, no Effect schema needed.
2. **Lint**: `bun lint` must pass — no new dependencies added.
3. **Manual smoke test**:
   - Open Settings → Appearance; three theme rows with swatches appear.
   - Select "T3 Midnight" → page background shifts to deep blue-purple, `.dark` class present on `<html>`.
   - Select "T3 Light" → page shifts to white, `.dark` class absent.
   - Reload page → selected theme persists (localStorage `t3code:color-theme:v1`).
   - Open second tab → theme changes sync cross-tab.
   - Existing dark/light/system radio buttons still work independently.
4. **Flash test**: Hard-reload; theme should apply before first paint (no white-flash when midnight is selected).

